For a married couple to have a woman change back to their maiden name commands a lot of attention, particularly for celebrities. This was the same for media personality Mpho and the retired soccer player Reneilwe Letsholonyane who as a result of this, have been a subject of speculation after Mpho changed back to her maiden name on all her social platforms. Rumors swirling around revealed that the pair may have called their marriage quits as Mpho suddenly became Maboi. Mpho and Letsholonyane who share children together celebrated their 3rd-anniversary in 2021 and offered a fervent gratitude for the years spent together. Their display of a happy family gave people couple goals as their marriage seemed to be flourishing. In a post that was shared by Mpho a year ago on her social platforms gave words of appreciation to her husband. “ I love you today, tomorrow, and always... “Over a decade of loving you and 3 years as your wife. Through the ups and the downs, I will continue to choose you, till we are old and grey. Happy anniversary my love.” Neither of the pair has openly spoken about the trouble that may have surrounded their marriage. While it is believed there is smoke in their marriage the SABC1 Sports anchor turned to Instagram to acknowledge Reneilwe “Yeye”  for Father's day. In a series of photos that included other people Mpho said, “ Happy Fathers Day to all amazing fathers and father figures. May your day be as blessed as you are a blessing.” she shared